1. *Bežiš* od odgovornosti kad god ti nešto ne uspe. (You run away from responsibility whenever something doesn't work out for you.)
2. Zašto *bežiš* od istine? (Why do you avoid the truth?)
3. *Bežiš* od problema umesto da ih rešavaš. (You're escaping from problems instead of solving them.)
4. Kada je počela kiša, svi su *bežali* u zatvoreni prostor. (When the rain started, everyone was running to a shelter.)
5. Ne možeš *bežati* od posledica svojih postupaka. (You can't run away from the consequences of your actions.)
6. Da li si primetio da mi stalno *beži* pogled kada pokušavam da ga pogledam u oči? (Did you notice that my gaze keeps avoiding yours when I try to look you in the eyes?)
7. Naša mačka često *beži* od drugih mačaka u komšiluku. (Our cat often runs away from other cats in the neighborhood.)
8. Da ne *bežimo* od teme, vratimo se na glavnu tačku dnevnog reda. (Let's not deviate from the topic and return to the main agenda item.)
9. Kada se ne oseća dobro, moj sin obično *beži* u svoju sobu da se odmori. (When he doesn't feel well, my son usually retreats to his room to rest.)
10. Moja baka je nekada volela da *beži* u prirodu i uživa u dugim šetnjama. (My grandma used to love escaping to nature and enjoying long walks.)